<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The paralectotype of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. lucens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="lucens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. lucens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mentioned above bears a lectotype label by L. Zombori (&quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="Lectotypus" lsidName="Lectotypus" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="genus">Lectotypus</taxonomicName>
♂ 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus lucens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus lucens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<normalizedToken originalValue="…">...</normalizedToken>
] des. Zombori 1980&quot;), but Zombori never published a lectotype designation. Although the paralectotype male has a handwritten label, most probably by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
